name: fifteen52 RSL Tarmac Cast Monoblock Wheel
description:
fifteen52 RSL Tarmac Cast Monoblock Wheel.

fifteen52 RSL Tarmac
-Size: 18x9.5" & 18x9.5"
-Bolt Pattern: 5x100, 5x112, 5x114.3, 5x120, Custom*
-Offset: varies per fitment
-Color: Brilliant Silver, Gloss White, Custom*
-Lip Size: None!
-Lug Type: Conical Seat

Completely flat-faced with a deep, vertical drop center; this clean, simple design offers a modern motorsport look. Based on the original 18x8.5 Tarmac, the 18x9.5 will allow for many more fitment options!

For a staggered set, add 2 of the narrow width and 2 of the wider width.  See related items for more size options.

Some finishes shown are optional and not all finish/fitment combinations are in stock at all times.

name: fifteen52 RSL TurboMac by Ken Block Forged Monoblock Wheel
description:
fifteen52 RSL TurboMac by Ken Block Forged Monoblock Wheel.

As seen in Ken Block's Gymkhana SIX video,* his new 18x9" TurboMac wheel was actually co-designed by fifteen52 and KB himself.

Essentially a Tarmac (KB's previous signature wheel design) center with a vented 'turbo' ring, why we call it the TurboMac should need no explanation.

Built from solid 6061 forged aluminum billets, this is a very strong and relatively lightweight motorsports-quality wheel.

Custom built to your PCD, offset, and center bore and offered with the world-famous '52' 3D center cap.

*Turbo-fan wheel covers (as seen in the video) are not included.

name: fifteen52 Forged 3-piece Alexi Classic Wheel
description:
fifteen52 Forged 3-piece Alexi Classic Wheel.

The Alexi - a special wheel inspired by a truly special friend.  A portion of each sale of the Alexi wheel goes to charity.

Our 3-piece wheels use forged 6061 aluminum centers and forged classic stepped lips and barrels.

Available in 15" to 20" diameters and almost any width and finish, we're talking truly custom wheels made to your exact specs!

3-piece wheels are built to order and not kept on the shelf. Because of the truly custom nature of these wheels online pricing and ordering is not possible, but the wheels can be built in about 4-6 weeks.

**Special Order**

The quality is exceptional, these are solid carbon fibre multiple layered carbon, not just "skinned" bumpers. 

Moulded from an original set of bumpers and end caps which were sanded down, smoothed, primered and then moulded to make a cast for the new carbon fibre pieces. 

Can also be supplied as end caps only.

Made in UK
